  "prompt": "Which laptop is the best one to buy for gaming under 35000?",
  "response": "As of my last update, finding a gaming laptop under \u20b935,000 can be quite challenging, as most gaming-capable laptops typically come at a higher price point due to the requirements for a dedicated graphics card and other performance components. However, there are some options that you might consider, particularly if you're willing to compromise on some gaming performance for a better price.\n\nHere are a few options you might explore:\n\n1. **Acer Aspire 7** (If available on sale)\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 5 or Intel Core i5\n   - **Graphics**: NVIDIA GTX 1650\n   - **RAM**: 8GB (upgradeable)\n   - **Storage**: 512GB SSD (or upgrade options)\n\n2. **HP Pavilion Gaming Laptop**\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 5\n   - **Graphics**: GTX 1650 or integrated graphics (lower performance)\n   - **RAM**: 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 512GB SSD or a hybrid option\n\n3. **Lenovo Ideapad Gaming 3 (older models)**\n   - **Processor**: AMD Ryzen 5 or Intel Core i5 (older generation)\n   - **Graphics**: GTX 1650 (if you can find an older model around this price)\n   - **RAM**: 8GB\n   - **Storage**: 512GB SSD\n\n4. **Asus VivoBook Gaming (older models)**\n   - Similar specs as above but watching for historical sales might lead you to a variant within your budget.\n\n### Key Considerations:\n\n- **Integrated Graphics**: If you cannot find a dedicated GPU within the price range, consider laptops with strong integrated graphics (like AMD Ryzen 5 series) which can handle lighter games reasonably well.\n  \n- **Refurbished Models**: Consider looking at refurbished or older generation models which might offer better specs for the price.\n\n- **Sales and Discounts**: Always keep an eye on festivals and sale seasons (like Diwali or Black Friday) for potential discounts.\n\n- **Upgrade Potential**: Check if you can upgrade RAM and storage later to prolong the lifespan of your laptop.\n\n### Conclusion:\nAs the market is constantly changing, I recommend checking the latest reviews and comparisons for any new models released under \u20b935,000. Websites that aggregate tech reviews like NotebookCheck or even customer reviews on e-commerce platforms like Amazon and Flipkart can provide current insights and help you make a decision.",
